Shake Shack today is valued at more than US$3 billion, but it had very humble origins – a single hot dog cart. So how did this happen?
Danny Meyer was deeply interested in restaurants from a young age, and turned down law school to enter a low-prestige, high-risk industry – against most people’s advice and against his father’s wishes.
And he entered not from a position of theory and intellect, but by actually working at restaurants in junior positions - understanding the cooking and serving of good food.



